# Local Development Environment Variables
#
# Copy this file to .dev.vars and fill in your values.
# This file is used by `wrangler dev` for local development.
# Never commit .dev.vars to version control!

# Required: API key for LLM service (default: Venice.ai)
# Get one at: https://venice.ai/
LLM_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

# Required: Admin API key for /scrape endpoint
# Generate a secure random string
ADMIN_API_KEY=your_admin_api_key_here

# Optional: LLM Configuration
# These allow you to use a different LLM provider or model.
# Note: Only Venice.ai has been tested. Other OpenAI-compatible APIs should work but are unverified.
# LLM_API_URL=https://api.venice.ai/api/v1/chat/completions
# LLM_MODEL=llama-3.3-70b
# LLM_TIMEOUT_MS=15000
# LLM_MAX_RETRIES=1

# Optional: Email notification settings (for scrape failure alerts)
# SMTP2GO_API_KEY=your_smtp2go_api_key_here
# NOTIFICATION_EMAIL_TO=your-email@example.com
# NOTIFICATION_EMAIL_FROM=noreply@your-domain.com
